cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.MA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper focuses on the design of radio resource management for high-speed railway communications, which is a networking problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses channel models and characteristics of HSR wireless communications, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper is primarily concerned with the design of communication systems for HSR, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses mobility management, which can be viewed as a multiagent system problem. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses power control and resource allocation, which are related to control theory and system optimization.
